	  </p>
	  <p>
		<img src="/assets/sweetcorn.jpg" img class="img-responsive pull-right" width= "400" Hspace="10" Vspace="10">  
		It's sweetcorn time! And trust me, you've never tasted proper sweetcorn until it's been picked seconds before steaming and eating straight away - truly delicious. So, here's how we do it:
		<ol>
		<li>First of all - this is one of the few crops that need some consideration as to their location. They need lots of warmth and sunshine, good quality soil and to be planted in a block to aid polination. So dig in some soil improver, compost or manure before you plant. </li>
		<li>Sow the seeds directly into the soil. Make holes at least 30cm apart, a couple of cms deep and drop a seed in each hole. Fill the holes with soil, and water well. It's important to keep them damp - that means watering every day during the heat of summer. </li>
		<li>The seeds will need about 18 degrees in order to start growing, so if it's chilly where you are, cover the soil with a plastic sheet to keep them toasty warm. You should start to see your seedlings sprout in around 2 weeks, and if the are gaps in your block after three weeks then fill them in with your spare seeds. </li>
	</ol>
