	  <p>
		<img src="/assets/french.jpg" img class="img-responsive" Vspace="10" >  
		French Beans produce lots of beans over a good few weeks so can make a plentiful and reliable crop. Plant two beans every 25cm and, if doing more than one row, keep rows about 75cm apart. French bean plants will grow tall and the shoots will need something to climb. You will need to make a few, long rows rather than many short ones, and in a position where you can either build a bamboo A-frame or against a trellised wall. 
