	  <p>
		<img src= "/assets/courgette.jpg" img class= "img-responsive pull-right" Hspace="10" width="240" Vspace="10">  
		You should now be beginning to see some flowers and baby courgettes on your plant. Courgettes produce a lot of fruit so harvest them when they're small and keep on top of them: it only takes a couple of days for them to swell up to marrows and are then very difficult to eat as fast as they grow! The flowers are also tasty, so don't throw them away when you pick your fruit - chuck them in a stir fry instead. When picking, simple twist and pull, but be careful - the leaves and fruit have tiny hairs on that can irritate your skin, so wash your hands after. 
